<section class="hero"><div class="hero-inner"><div class="breadcrumb"><a href="index.html">SFGS</a> <span>/</span> Admission <span>/</span> Admission Criteria</div><h2>Admission <em>Criteria</em></h2><div class="hero-divider"></div><p class="hero-tagline">Three carefully designed stages — application, aptitude test, and panel interview — to identify the future of SFGS.</p></div></section>
<div class="motto-strip"><span class="star">★</span><p>Application · Aptitude · Interview</p><span class="star">★</span></div>
<div class="main-wrap"><main class="content">
<p>Admission to St Francis Girls Suwerwa is <strong>highly competitive</strong>, and prospective students must meet our set criteria to be considered. The admission process takes place in <strong>three carefully designed stages</strong> — each with its own unique requirements — beginning immediately after KCPE results are released.</p>

<div class="stages-intro">
  <h3>Three Stages, One Goal</h3>
  <p>To identify students who will thrive academically, grow spiritually, and lead with integrity at St Francis Girls Suwerwa.</p>
</div>

<div class="stages-flow">

  <div class="stage-item">
    <div class="stage-number">1</div>
    <div class="stage-card">
      <span class="stage-tag">⌛ Stage One</span>
      <h3>Application &amp; Document Review</h3>
      <p>Students submit their application forms together with required supporting documents. These are then scrutinized by the admissions office, and only those who meet the minimum academic qualifications proceed to the next stage.</p>
      <strong style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--navy);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif">Required Documents:</strong>
      <div class="docs-list">
        <div class="doc-pill">Completed application form</div>
        <div class="doc-pill">Copy of birth certificate</div>
        <div class="doc-pill">School transcripts / report cards</div>
        <div class="doc-pill">Other relevant documents</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="stage-item">
    <div class="stage-number">2</div>
    <div class="stage-card">
      <span class="stage-tag">🧠 Stage Two</span>
      <h3>The Aptitude Test</h3>
      <p>All eligible students are invited to take an aptitude test set by the school's examination board. The test aims at evaluating the candidate's cognitive abilities, language proficiency, and mathematical skills — and is usually taken within the school's own facilities.</p>
      <strong style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--navy);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif">Areas Tested:</strong>
      <div class="eval-grid">
        <div class="eval-chip">🧮 Cognitive Ability</div>
        <div class="eval-chip">📖 Language Proficiency</div>
        <div class="eval-chip">➕ Mathematical Skills</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="stage-item">
    <div class="stage-number">3</div>
    <div class="stage-card">
      <span class="stage-tag">🎤 Stage Three</span>
      <h3>The Panel Interview</h3>
      <p>Shortlisted students are called for an interview with the school's admissions committee. The panel evaluates each student's life skills, character, and potential — taking into account academic achievements, extra-curricular activities, community service, and leadership qualities.</p>
      <strong style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--navy);font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif">What the Panel Evaluates:</strong>
      <div class="assessment-grid">
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">1</span>Academic record</div>
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">2</span>Co-curricular activities</div>
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">3</span>Community service</div>
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">4</span>Leadership skills</div>
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">5</span>Character &amp; integrity</div>
        <div class="assess-item"><span class="num">6</span>Personal potential</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<h2 class="section-heading">Final Decision &amp; Notification</h2>
<p>The school's admissions committee makes the final decision based on a combined evaluation across all three stages of the process. Successful applicants are then notified directly, and they may proceed to pay their admission fee and finalize their admission.</p>

<div class="timing-banner">
  <div class="timing-icon">📅</div>
  <div>
    <h4>When Does Admission Open?</h4>
    <p>The admission process at SFGS begins <strong>immediately after KCPE results are released</strong>. Stay tuned via our notice board for exact dates and deadlines each year.</p>
  </div>
</div>
